# Chain rule and implicit differentiation

For a composite,

$$
\frac{d}{dx}f(g(x))=f'(g(x))g'(x).
$$

If $x^2+y^2=25$, differentiate both sides with respect to $x$:

$$
2x+2y\frac{dy}{dx}=0,
$$

so $dy/dx=-x/y$ where $y\ne0$.


> **Study habit:** translate every formula into a sentence about quantities and units.

:::mcf-end

